Uttar Pradesh
Dec 09, 2014
Rape
Description:
			A 20-year-old girl has accused her classmate of raping her repeatedly over two years on the pretext of marriage, police said today.

Yesterday, a case was registered at Mahila Thana here against the 22-year-old youth who studied in the same degree college as the victim, police said.

Two years ago the victim had shifted into a rented accomodation in a locality falling under Shahjadnagar police station, following which she came into contact with the youth, police said, adding, the accused then established sexual relations with the victim on the pretext of marriage.

Later, when the girl urged him to solemnise the marriage but he refused, after which she approached the police, they added.


